node.text: Summer is officially here—how are you making the most of it? We caught up with West Elm Insiders Rachel Owens (@rachelamyowens), Steven Fingar (@stevenfingar), Carol de Mauro (@caroldemauro) and Joanne Rivera (@rhausliving) to chat about the projects they’re tackling this summer, their latest product crushes this season and more. Read more about what’s trending this season at westelm.com/summer2021

node.title: The Summer Scoop with West Elm Insiders

node.text: Gingham, plaid and stripes never go out of style, but textiles designer Heather Taylor is here to make them feel fresh. Check out her exclusive new collection for  West Elm - link in bio. #HTHxWestElm

node.text: “I like to break the rules and push boundaries,” says designer @sarahshermansamuel. For this Design Challenge build-out, watch as she turns our blank-slate set into a kids’ bedroom-playroom hybrid that goes big on whimsical architectural details, playful pattern-mixing and room for creativity. Tap the link in our bio to get the look and to see more of Sarah's tips for creating an epic, imagination-station kids’ space. #WestElmKids

node.title: Design Challenge with Sarah Sherman Samuel

node.text: In Guadalajara City, two artisan collectives called @impercrisa and @centralcvsj practice the ancient art of glassblowing, a skill set shared across generations. This video is part of West Elm’s La Mesa collection, a partnership with 8 artisan groups across Mexico to celebrate Mexican culture and create sustainable income for 510 local artisans, helping preserve their heritage craft techniques. Special thanks to master glass blowers Leopoldo Fonseca and Antonio Perez, @diegolivero and @gabrielccoco. Tap the link in our bio to learn more.
